        <div id="tags">
            <h2>What do the tags in our website mean?</h2>
            <div class="tag">
                <h3>Treats patient respectfully as autonomous individuals</h3>
                <p>
                    The doctor will treat you as an independent autonomous individual irrespective of your caste, creed, religion, marital status, sexual preferences and choices. <br/>
                    They will look for solutions to your pain and illness without advocating marriage or pregnancy. <br/>
                    They will respectfully and non-judgmentally ask about and accept your sexual activity and history, regardless of marital status. <br/>
                    They will discuss choosing to stay celibate or child-free positively and non-judgementally. <br/>
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="tag">
                <h3>Trans-friendly</h3>
                <p>
                    The doctor will make trans men, trans women and other people who don't identify as cis female feel welcomed and 
                    discuss gender dysphoria related medical issues positively and non-judgmentally. <br/>
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="tag">
                <h3>Queer-friendly</h3>
                <p>
                    The doctor will discuss queer sexuality positively and non-judgementally.<br/>
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="tag">
                <h3>Treats survivors of abuse sensitively and respectfully</h3>
                <p>
                    The doctor will welcome survivors of incest, sexual and domestic abuse, and discuss healing from rape and sexual trauma
                     sensitively and respectfully.<br/>
                </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tag">
                <h3>AIDS/Other STDs-friendly</h3>
                <p>
                    TThe doctor will welcome people with AIDS or other sexually transmittable diseases without judgement.<br/>
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="tag">
                <h3>Body Positive</h3>
                <p>
                    The doctor will examine your body thoroughly and professionally without making you feel ugly, embarrassed, ashamed or uncomfortable.<br/>
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="tag">
                <h3>Will not demand partner/parentâ€™s consent/approval</h3>
                <p>
                    The doctor will keep your information private, even from your parents or partner and will not demand permission/consent 
                    from parents or partner for conducting medical procedures (for legal adults).<br/>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

